{
  "text": "Apparent viscosity investigation at the middle shear rates is useful for sensory and mouth feel evaluation (1-100 s Table 3) . The consistency coefficient (K) of the samples varied between 21.59 and 135.2Pa s n and K values of samples were found to be significantly (P<0.05) different with respect to the mentioned Power law parameters. The highest K value observed in F4 (9 % WGPI), that indicates a more viscose fluid [CITATION_1] .",
